<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFB6FFA4C6A45707FE05F823" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="204" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB6FFA5C6A45707FF58F8A2" blockId="2.[151,1437,1588,2010]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB6FFA5C6A45707FE9FF9EE" bold="true" box="[151,274,1588,1614]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Apical seta longer than maximum width of palpus; setal palisade 2/3 length of mid tibia; setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half; tergite VI reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter with 4 long and 4–5 short setulae; sternite VI clearly defined, with 4 very strong pin-shaped setae and some fine, long setulae; dorsum of oviscape with 3–4 short setulae on sub-apex of each side; venter of oviscape with 12–16 fine, long and transversely-inclined setulae arranged in two longitudinal rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB6FFA5C6F4563FFDC6F832" blockId="2.[151,1437,1588,2010]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB6FFA5C6F4563FFEA8F886" bold="true" box="[199,293,1804,1830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Female.</emphasis>
Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB6FFA5C748563FFE5CF886" box="[379,465,1804,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-79@3.[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–F. Pseudacteon quadrisetalis Liu et Cai, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) dark brown, with about 12–14 setulae. Frons with 2 pairs of supra-antennal setae, upper pair as high as lower fronto-orbital setae. Second row of frontal setae clearly concave, all four setae are equally distanced. Flagellomere 1 brown, subglobose. Palpus pale, very lightly tinged brown, with 4 long setae, apical one longer than maximum width of palpus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB6FFA4C6F456AFFE59FEBD" blockId="2.[151,1437,1588,2010]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,150,285]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="204" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
Thorax brown. Scutellum with a pair of setae, posterior twice length of anterior. Legs yellowish brown. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres 0.81: 0.77: 0.63: 0.61: 1, with all five bearing a setal palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB6FFA5C28E56F3FA99F87A" box="[1213,1300,1984,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-79@3.[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–F. Pseudacteon quadrisetalis Liu et Cai, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade extends 2/3 length along mid tibia and comprising 35–40 modified setulae (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB7FFA4C22D51A4FBFAFF11" box="[1054,1143,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-79@3.[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–F. Pseudacteon quadrisetalis Liu et Cai, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB7FFA4C5B95188FC52FF75" box="[906,991,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-79@3.[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–F. Pseudacteon quadrisetalis Liu et Cai, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB7FFA4C2725188FB1BFF75" box="[1089,1174,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-79@3.[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–F. Pseudacteon quadrisetalis Liu et Cai, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB7FFA4C2C05188FA15FF75" box="[1267,1432,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1549999999999998" metricValueMax="1.17" metricValueMin="1.14" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" unit="mm" value="1.1549999999999998" valueMax="1.17" valueMin="1.14">1.14–1.17 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB7FFA4C6EC51EDFE08FF59" box="[223,389,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" metricValueMax="5.8999999999999995" metricValueMin="5.699999999999999" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" unit="mm" value="0.58" valueMax="0.59" valueMin="0.57">0.57–0.59 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.51. Costal index 0.38–0.39. Costal ratio 1.96: 1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB7FFA4C2DF51ECFAD9FF59" box="[1260,1364,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
. Alula with 3 setae. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FFB7FFA4C6A45715FADAF9C3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" startId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" targetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB7FFA4C6A45715FADAF9C3" blockId="3.[151,1436,1574,1635]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB7FFA4C6A45715FEC2F99E" bold="true" box="[151,335,1574,1598]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">FIGURES 1A–F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFB7FFA4C7655714FD5BF99F" authority="Liu et Cai" authorityName="Liu et Cai" box="[342,726,1575,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrisetalis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB7FFA4C7655714FDEEF99F" box="[342,611,1575,1599]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Pseudacteon quadrisetalis</emphasis>
Liu 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB7FFA4C4A55714FD25F99E" box="[662,680,1575,1598]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">et</emphasis>
Cai
</taxonomicName>
, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB7FFA4C6F457A2FC77F8FF" blockId="3.[151,1436,1681,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
Abdomen. Tergites brown with sparse minute setulae. Tergites II–V very much broader than long, but progressively narrowing from tergite II backwards. Tergite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB7FFA4C5085786FC2CF96F" box="[827,929,1717,1743]" captionStart="FIGURES 24" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1388,188,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-19@33.[190,1398,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 24A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. quadrisetalis Liu et Cai; C–D. P. trapeziformis Zhang et Liu; E–F. P. inticlinatus sp. nov.; G–H. P. setipalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya; I–J. P. reticulatus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559613/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Fig. 24A</figureCitation>
) reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each side bears 4 long and 4–5 short setulae at rear margin. Venter brown. Sternite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB7FFA4C29757EAFA8FF953" box="[1188,1282,1753,1779]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-79@3.[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–F. Pseudacteon quadrisetalis Liu et Cai, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Figs. 1F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB7FFA4C32357EAFAB2F953" box="[1296,1343,1753,1779]" captionStart="FIGURES 24" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1388,188,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-19@33.[190,1398,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 24A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. quadrisetalis Liu et Cai; C–D. P. trapeziformis Zhang et Liu; E–F. P. inticlinatus sp. nov.; G–H. P. setipalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya; I–J. P. reticulatus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559613/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">24B</figureCitation>
) clearly defined, with 4 very strong pin-shaped setae and some fine and long setulae. Oviscape brown. The dorsum of the oviscape arched, with 3–4 short setulae on sub-apex of each side. The venter of the oviscape with 12–16 fine, long and transversely-inclined setulae arranged in two longitudinal rows (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB7FFA4C5AB5676FC61F8FF" box="[920,1004,1861,1887]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1574,1598]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-79@3.[151,1435,306,1548]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–F. Pseudacteon quadrisetalis Liu et Cai, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
